\f4\b\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 Seated bodhisattva (left attendant of a triad)\uc0\u8232 
\f1\b0 Joseon dynasty (1392\'961910), ca. mid-17th century\uc0\u8232 Gilt wood
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 Mary Griggs Burke Collection, Gift of the Mary and Jackson Burke Foundation, 2015 (2015.300.301a\'96c)
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 This figure is a bodhisattva\'97an enlightened being who has compassionately chosen to remain on earth and guide mortals toward nirvana. X-rays reveal cavities in the statue\'92s head and torso corresponding to rectangular outlines visible from the back. Although the torso is empty, the head contains a bokjang (enclosed ritual offering), a scrunched fibrous material similar to that in the Kashyapa displayed nearby. The figure\'92s hands, carved separately, are removable and absent in the scan.
\f0\fs24 \
