\f4\b\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 Needle cases and bobbins\uc0\u8232 
\f1\b0 Goryeo dynasty (918\'961392), 12th\'9613th century\uc0\u8232 Partially gilt silver inlaid with niello; silver
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 Rogers Fund, 1917 and 1922 (17.175.34a, b; 22.141.25)
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 These compact needle cases and bobbins exemplify the relationship between form and function. The hollow inner cylinders provide needle storage, and the segments allow the user to wind different threads onto the same spool. One end of the interior bobbin functions as the top of the outer container. Niello flowers and scrolling as well as densely stamped scallop motifs appear on the open case. Incised arabesques and flora adorn the hidden bobbin.
\f0\fs24 \
