\f4\b\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 Incense box\uc0\u8232 
\f1\b0 Joseon dynasty (1392\'961910), 14th\'9615th century\uc0\u8232 Iron inlaid with gold and silver
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 Rogers Fund, 1921 (21.117.3)
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 From its form to its surface decoration, this incense box with Buddhist elements exemplifies intricate construction and design. On the lid, a gold-inlaid flaming lotus cradles a Buddhist sutra above swirling silver waves (enlarged on the glass). The gilt double-gourd vessel attached to the lid echoes the shape of the three feet and the support below the handle. On the box\'92s underside and edges, elaborate and interlacing silver-inlaid geometric patterns have darkened over time.
\f0\fs24 \
