\f4\b\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 Filigree scent container\uc0\u8232 
\f1\b0 Joseon dynasty (1392\'961910), 19th century\uc0\u8232 Silver
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 Rogers Fund, 1922 (22.141.29)
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 Delicate phoenixes, openwork spirals, and interlacing rings adorn this filigree container for dried flowers and herbs. Once a scented accessory, the vessel would have hung from a hanbok (Korean dress) or a handheld fan. The closing mechanism takes advantage of gravity and the long tradition of maedeup, decorative knotting. When released, the container naturally slides toward the bottom knot, which acts as a stopper.
\f0\fs24 \
