\f4\b\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 Tobacco box\uc0\u8232 
\f1\b0 Joseon dynasty (1392\'961910), 19th century\uc0\u8232 Iron inlaid with silver; brass fittings
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 Rogers Fund, 1922 (22.78)
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 Smoking became widespread in the late Joseon period, prompting the production of specialized paraphernalia such as this iron tobacco box with silver inlay. Though the lid appears simple\'97a thin iron sheet with a bent edge\'97it conceals an interesting locking mechanism. The button near the handle releases a catch on the underside, allowing the cover to slide open. Bird and flower scenes, a stylized character, and dense silver-inlaid geometric motifs form a rich array of auspicious symbols.
