\f4\b\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 Talisman\uc0\u8232 
\f1\b0 Joseon dynasty (1392\'961910), 19th century\uc0\u8232 Stone
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 Rogers Fund, 1917 (17.175.35)
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667 This talisman\'92s bold curving lines dynamically depict a dragon amid the clouds. Flying in from the top, the creature\'92s body snakes downward, its face and lively eyes nearly at the center. In contrast, the back of the stone (pictured here) bears three sets of five circles along with small scalelike patterns, perhaps an abstract rendering of a dragon\'92s skin. While the object\'92s usage is unknown, its size allows for it to be held in a hand or pocket.
\f0\fs24 \
