\f1\b0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Ancient ritual bronzes, used in ceremonies\uc0\u8232 to honor ancestors, have been central to\u8232 political life throughout Korean history. As\u8232 symbols of power and authority, they were\u8232 often decorated with dragon motifs. The\u8232 scene depicted on this mirror highlights\u8232 this connection. Two dragons fly downward,\u8232 flanking and animatedly peering at a\u8232 steaming bronze tripod cauldron. Clouds\u8232 and a foliated rim embellish the border.
