\f1\b0\fs29\fsmilli14667 This mirror\'92s five segments depict com-\uc0\u8232 ponents of Daoist and Confucian cosmology\u8232 that were adopted throughout East Asia.\u8232 The central animals represent the five\u8232 cardinal directions (ohaeng), followed by\u8232 the Eight Trigrams (palgwae) with the\u8232 Ten Heavenly Stems (cheongan), then the\u8232 Twelve Zodiac Animals. The fourth register\u8232 depicts thirty-six animals, and the\u8232 outermost band has the twenty-four solar\u8232 terms (jeolgi) in seal script, with six terms\u8232 assigned to each of the four seasons.
