\f1\b0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Buddhism arrived in Korea in the fourth\uc0\u8232 century, and by the sixth century, became\u8232 the peninsula\'92s predominant belief system.\u8232 It was the state religion during the Goryeo\u8232 period, when the arts flourished under\u8232 royal and temple patronage. Buddhist\u8232 mantras commonly appeared on secular\u8232 and popular objects. This mirror bears\u8232 sixteen Sanskrit characters on the inner\u8232 band and twenty on the outer, some\u8232 of which comprise \'93Om Mani Padme Hum,\'94\u8232 a mantra chanted to gain enlightenment.
